&gt;                     My guess is that your browser is set up to use an HTTP
&gt;                 proxy, and
&gt;                     that proxy is doing everything (including name
&gt;         lookups) for
&gt;                 the browser.
&gt;
&gt;                     But, the machine itself can&#39;t do domain lookups. (Or
&gt;                 perhaps: can
&gt;                     only do a small number of internal/approved domain
&gt;         lookups.)
&gt;                 This
&gt;                     will need to be resolved in the machine&#39;s
&gt;         configuration for
&gt;                 Heritrix
&gt;                     to work.
&gt;
&gt;                     Heritrix can direct HTTP requests through a
&gt;         configured proxy
&gt;                 -- but
&gt;                     expects to be able to do DNS lookups itself. It
&gt;         would take a
&gt;                 code
&gt;                     change to enable skipping DNS lookups when an HTTP
&gt;         proxy is
&gt;                 to be
&gt;                     used, and it would mean there would be no record of the
&gt;                 actual IP
&gt;                     address contacted (which would be a problem for our
&gt;         usual
&gt;                     archival-record use, though would make sense in other
&gt;                 applications).
&gt;
&gt;                     - Gordon @ IA
